A man has been killed when his light motor vehicle rear-ended a truck on the N1 South-bound before the John Vorster turnoff in Centurion on Friday.The patient is believed to be in his 40s.On arrival, paramedics found the truck parked in the emergency lane while the light motor vehicle was found in the fast lane of the highway.ER24&#8217;s Russel Meiring stated that paramedics found the body of a man lying trapped inside the vehicle. Sadly, there was nothing that paramedics could do for the man and he was declared dead due to his multiple fatal injuries, said Meiring.It is said that the driver of the truck was assessed and found to have escaped injury.The cause of the collision is still known. Local authorities investigating the collision further.-TNA Reporter